WEBVTT

00:07.607 --> 00:09.209
[school bell rings]

00:10.343 --> 00:12.212
- I'm sure
you're all wondering

00:12.245 --> 00:14.314
why I'm not up for
"Most Likely to Succeed."

00:14.347 --> 00:17.684
As editor of this paper,
I had to recuse myself.

00:17.717 --> 00:19.285
- I got nominated
for "Whitest."

00:19.319 --> 00:21.588
Is that bad?
It's not, right?

00:21.621 --> 00:23.456
- How could it be bad,
you know?

00:23.490 --> 00:26.126
I mean, look at how cool
the sword you're drawing is.

00:26.159 --> 00:28.428
- It's not just any sword.
It's Excalibur,

00:28.461 --> 00:30.397
the most famous sword
of all time.

00:37.704 --> 00:39.372
[apple rolling]

00:43.209 --> 00:45.679
- [groans]
Ohh...

00:48.648 --> 00:52.352
- Should we be starting
to shut up now, Boss?

00:52.385 --> 00:53.486
<i>[Ramones'</i>
<i>"Listen to My Heart"]</i>

00:53.520 --> 00:55.255
<i>- One, two, three, four!</i>

00:55.288 --> 00:57.590
<i>- ♪ Next time,</i>
<i>I'll listen to my heart ♪</i>

00:57.624 --> 01:00.460
<i>♪ Next time,</i>
<i>well, I'll be smart ♪</i>

01:00.493 --> 01:07.400
<i>♪ </i>

01:07.434 --> 01:10.670
<i>[light music]</i>

01:10.704 --> 01:16.376
♪

01:16.409 --> 01:18.511
- I'm up for "Most Original,"

01:18.545 --> 01:21.581
the category formerly known as
"Biggest Freak."

01:21.614 --> 01:23.350
- Eduardo and I
have been nominated

01:23.383 --> 01:25.251
for "Best Friends" again

01:25.285 --> 01:28.288
but we don't need a trophy
to confirm our bond.

01:28.321 --> 01:29.689
- Yeah, that's 'cause
you know you're gonna lose

01:29.723 --> 01:32.258
to Ashley Dorfman
and Amanda Jackson.

01:32.292 --> 01:35.462
- Ashlanda!
Ugh, love them.

01:35.495 --> 01:37.664
- I didn't get nominated
for anything.

01:37.697 --> 01:39.532
- Me neither.

01:39.566 --> 01:42.235
But Craig Donovan made the list
for "Best Singer."

01:42.268 --> 01:44.204
Sure, if you like a tenor
who pushes!

01:44.237 --> 01:47.640
- These, uh, superlatives
will never matter.

01:47.674 --> 01:49.609
Nothing matters.

01:49.642 --> 01:52.545
We're all just rapidly
decaying meat bags

01:52.579 --> 01:54.247
we patch together
with duct tape

01:54.280 --> 01:55.615
till the bottom falls out.

01:55.648 --> 01:59.319
- Is your meat bag okay,
Mr. G?

01:59.352 --> 02:01.588
- Well, we'll find out
after my colonoscopy.

02:01.621 --> 02:03.790
I don't know if I have, like,
a family history of anything

02:03.823 --> 02:05.325
'cause I don't speak
to my dad.

02:05.358 --> 02:06.693
So to be safe,

02:06.726 --> 02:09.763
I gotta drink this muck
for 24 hours

02:09.796 --> 02:12.399
then get my butt probed.

02:12.432 --> 02:14.701
- I'm surprised that you're
opening up to us, Mr. Griffin.

02:14.734 --> 02:16.569
- Yeah, well, you guys
don't count, you know.

02:16.603 --> 02:18.405
I'm hiding it from adults,

02:18.438 --> 02:19.839
people who don't play
Pogs all day

02:19.873 --> 02:22.442
while wondering
who shot Mr. Burns.

02:22.475 --> 02:24.644
- It's clear from your tone
that we've been savaged.

02:24.678 --> 02:27.681
But I wonder if you could do it
again with updated references.

02:27.714 --> 02:29.249
- I cannot.

02:29.282 --> 02:30.450
And now...

02:30.483 --> 02:31.651
[thud]

02:31.685 --> 02:32.686
I must leave you.

02:32.719 --> 02:35.855
[phones buzzing, chiming]

02:35.889 --> 02:37.624
- Buckle up, people.

02:37.657 --> 02:39.626
Amanda and Ashley
have had a fight!

02:39.659 --> 02:41.394
They're off the ballot.

02:41.428 --> 02:43.396
- This could be
our year!

02:43.430 --> 02:46.399
We could go down
in Whitlock history.

02:46.433 --> 02:48.268
Secret handshake time?

02:48.301 --> 02:49.869
- Gimme
that knuckle candy.

02:49.903 --> 02:51.738
[both whispering]
One, two, three.

02:51.771 --> 02:53.406
[laughs]

02:53.440 --> 02:56.509
- Hmm?
- I like his new boyfriend.

02:56.543 --> 02:59.546
- Hey, uh, Mary.
- Hey.

02:59.579 --> 03:01.648
- Do you remember
a few months back

03:01.681 --> 03:03.550
when, uh, we made
your grandma believe

03:03.583 --> 03:05.719
that I was a firefighter
named Cash

03:05.752 --> 03:07.554
and we were getting married
in a Catholic ceremony?

03:07.587 --> 03:09.622
- [chuckling] Yeah.
- Yeah, well, um,

03:09.656 --> 03:11.658
you kinda owe me.
I need a ride.

03:11.691 --> 03:13.593
- Yeah, sure.
- Okay.

03:13.626 --> 03:16.296
- Where do you need to go?
- Well, I don't wanna say.

03:16.329 --> 03:18.631
- Oh, hey, psst, I know
I'm not in this conversation,

03:18.665 --> 03:21.368
but why can't you
drive yourself?

03:21.401 --> 03:22.802
- I'm omitting that as well.

03:22.836 --> 03:24.504
- Oh.
- I'm obviously gonna know

03:24.537 --> 03:25.905
once we get to
the destination.

03:25.939 --> 03:27.807
Unless it's
a nondescript building.

03:27.841 --> 03:29.743
- It's a nondescript
building.

03:29.776 --> 03:31.511
- You know,
the more closed off you are,

03:31.544 --> 03:33.813
the more I just wanna
take my nails and just...

03:33.847 --> 03:35.782
[pops lips]
pry you open.

03:35.815 --> 03:38.618
You're like that one
closed pistachio.

03:38.651 --> 03:41.321
- You know what happens
to the open pistachios?

03:41.354 --> 03:43.356
They get eaten.

03:43.390 --> 03:44.491
- Well, see, that's the point.

03:44.524 --> 03:46.526
- Let us eat you,
little pistachio.

03:46.559 --> 03:48.795
- We will gain
your powers!

03:54.434 --> 03:57.337
- Who do you think you are,
Ellen's DJ?

03:57.370 --> 03:58.371
[sighs]

03:58.405 --> 04:05.311
<i>♪ </i>

04:20.827 --> 04:26.399
<i>♪ </i>

04:28.735 --> 04:31.671
- Ralph, you look pretty!

04:31.705 --> 04:33.673
Ooh, ya smell nice too.

04:33.707 --> 04:35.375
- Oh, well, you look pretty
spiffy yourself.

04:35.408 --> 04:36.509
Is that a new shirt?

04:36.543 --> 04:38.812
- Oh, gosh, no, this is my
grandfather's favorite shirt.

04:38.845 --> 04:40.647
He was buried in it.

04:40.680 --> 04:42.415
But then they reopened
the murder case, so--

04:42.449 --> 04:43.983
- Ooh!
There you are!

04:44.017 --> 04:46.486
Hi, Helen, hi, Ralph!

04:46.519 --> 04:49.723
I like it, so I'm gonna
put a class ring on it.

04:49.756 --> 04:51.691
[laughter]

04:51.725 --> 04:54.994
- I better squeeze you!
- Oh, you better!

04:55.028 --> 04:57.530
How are you?
[gasps] Look at your hair!

04:57.564 --> 04:58.965
- Hey, Marjorie, Marjorie,

04:58.998 --> 05:00.600
so weird you dropped by

05:00.633 --> 05:03.636
just as I...
was gettin' my twirl on!

05:03.670 --> 05:05.605
- Ralph, are those
devil sticks?

05:05.638 --> 05:06.873
- Yep.
I got 'em in the divorce.

05:06.906 --> 05:08.608
I am as single
as a $1 bill.

05:08.641 --> 05:09.943
- Mm!
- Mm-hmm.

05:09.976 --> 05:12.746
- What is that wonderful scent
that I'm smelling?

05:12.779 --> 05:14.547
- Dark Temptation
XL Body Spray.

05:14.581 --> 05:16.750
- Ha ha!
I knew it was you.

05:16.783 --> 05:18.752
I'm gonna get that
for my mailman next Christmas.

05:18.785 --> 05:20.420
That is so yummy on you.
- Yeah, yeah.

05:20.453 --> 05:22.022
- Look at this.
- Ooh!

05:22.055 --> 05:23.523
- Lookit. Lookit.
- Oh, I can tell.

05:23.556 --> 05:24.958
That looks like
something very special.

05:24.991 --> 05:25.992
- It's so special.
- Uh-- [stammers]

05:26.926 --> 05:28.028
- What you are looking at
is a lock of hair

05:28.061 --> 05:29.896
of the legendary

05:29.929 --> 05:31.798
Weird Al Yankovic.
- Ooh.

05:31.831 --> 05:33.800
- Marjorie, l-look,
this is a new trick.

05:33.833 --> 05:35.935
I call this The Body Scan--
watch this.

05:35.969 --> 05:38.905
Whoa!
And then...yaaaah--

05:38.938 --> 05:41.041
Opa!
- Ooh! Ah, that was great!

05:41.074 --> 05:42.942
- Been workin' on it.
- I was in line

05:42.976 --> 05:44.511
at JoAnn Fabrics,

05:44.544 --> 05:47.681
and who walks up
but the Bard himself?

05:47.714 --> 05:49.516
So I cut a little bit
of his mane

05:49.549 --> 05:50.917
when he wasn't paying
attention.

05:50.950 --> 05:52.819
- Oh, wow!

05:52.852 --> 05:54.654
This has truly made my day.

05:54.688 --> 05:56.623
- Oh, thank you.
Your hands have made my day.

05:56.656 --> 05:58.525
They're soft.
They're real soft.

05:58.558 --> 06:00.060
- Okay!
Well, I gotta go

06:00.093 --> 06:02.028
and peddle my wares.
[laughs]

06:02.062 --> 06:04.064
- Ah, it's so good.

06:04.097 --> 06:06.599
- I didn't want that
to end.

06:06.633 --> 06:09.569
<i>[tense music]</i>

06:09.602 --> 06:14.674
<i>♪ </i>

06:14.708 --> 06:17.677
<i>[Muzak playing]</i>

06:17.711 --> 06:24.651
<i>♪ </i>

06:26.586 --> 06:28.455
- Here you go.

06:30.724 --> 06:33.626
- Don't return forms
until they're fully complete.

06:33.660 --> 06:35.962
- I-I prefer to discuss
some of these privately

06:35.995 --> 06:37.630
with the doctor.
- [weird voice] Excuse me,

06:37.664 --> 06:39.065
is this where
you donate the urine?

06:39.099 --> 06:41.001
I'm a universal donor!
- What are you...doing?

06:41.034 --> 06:42.836
- [laughing]
- What are you doing?

06:42.869 --> 06:44.838
- You should have told me
it was a doctor's appointment.

06:44.871 --> 06:47.707
I've got a great butt guy.
Well, he's not a doctor,

06:47.741 --> 06:49.743
but he knows what
he's doin' back there.

06:49.776 --> 06:52.579
- Sir, your forms!

06:52.612 --> 06:54.114
First blank question.

06:54.147 --> 06:56.116
When was your last
evacuation?

06:56.149 --> 06:57.817
- Oh, this--
- Yeah, when was that thing?

06:57.851 --> 06:58.918
- Come on, don't--

06:58.952 --> 07:00.653
- I think we'd all
like to know.

07:00.687 --> 07:02.722
- This morning,
on the drive over.

07:02.756 --> 07:04.524
- What--at the gas station?
- Yep.

07:04.557 --> 07:05.725
- You said you were

07:05.759 --> 07:07.560
buying gum, you little liar!
- I did buy gum!

07:07.594 --> 07:08.862
- [loud laughing]
- Ma'am!

07:08.895 --> 07:10.830
Be quiet!

07:10.864 --> 07:12.866
Everything in this waiting room

07:12.899 --> 07:16.670
must be orderly.

07:16.703 --> 07:18.571
Select a crayon.

07:18.605 --> 07:22.909
Draw your stool so that
I can get on with my day.

07:22.942 --> 07:25.578
- Draw it?

07:25.612 --> 07:28.748
Oh, my God.

07:28.782 --> 07:30.550
Hey.

07:30.583 --> 07:34.854
Hey, Mary, I'm actually
pretty glad that you're here.

07:34.888 --> 07:37.657
Thanks for keeping this
a secret, so--

07:37.691 --> 07:39.859
Seacrest.

07:39.893 --> 07:41.761
Ryan Seacrest.

07:41.795 --> 07:44.097
- I would never
tell Seacrest.

07:44.130 --> 07:46.700
- I mean, I think
he's got enough on his plate.

07:46.733 --> 07:48.902
[laughs] You didn't
tell Lynette, did you?

07:48.935 --> 07:50.970
'Cause...I just want--

07:51.004 --> 07:53.173
I just want my butt
to be romantic.

07:53.206 --> 07:56.176
- No, for the 15th time,
I did not tell Lynette.

07:56.209 --> 07:58.144
- Okay, good.

07:58.178 --> 08:01.581
So you're the only one
that knows that--good.

08:01.614 --> 08:03.049
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

08:03.083 --> 08:05.018
- Knows what?
About your butt surgery?

08:05.051 --> 08:06.786
- Why is he face-up?

08:06.820 --> 08:08.188
- Hey, no, no.

08:08.221 --> 08:13.093
No one else knowing...
my Seacrests...

08:17.664 --> 08:19.799
<i>[light music]</i>

08:19.833 --> 08:21.701
- Can I ask you guys
a serious question?

08:21.735 --> 08:23.903
- Mm-hmm.
- Yeah.

08:23.937 --> 08:25.105
- Is this where
the baby comes out?

08:25.138 --> 08:26.639
[laughter]

08:26.673 --> 08:27.841
- Errrr...pffft!

08:27.874 --> 08:29.876
[laughter]
- You ladies

08:29.909 --> 08:31.678
are being very loud.

08:31.711 --> 08:32.912
- Ooh.
- Sorry.

08:32.946 --> 08:35.048
- Only the patient's ride
needs to be in here.

08:35.081 --> 08:36.216
- No, actually,
we are the ride,

08:36.249 --> 08:37.717
all three of us.
- Mm-hmm.

08:37.751 --> 08:39.719
- Well, maybe you'd be
more comfortable

08:39.753 --> 08:41.788
waiting someplace
more appropriate

08:41.821 --> 08:44.157
like a McDonald's Play Place.

08:44.190 --> 08:47.127
- Ooh, I know she did not
just tell this Burger Queen

08:47.160 --> 08:48.795
to go to McDonald's.

08:48.828 --> 08:50.030
- Mm-mm.
- Mm-mm.

08:50.063 --> 08:52.232
- You said something
about a lollipop.

08:52.265 --> 08:54.868
- Oh, there's our big guy!
- Aw.

08:54.901 --> 08:56.269
- Oh, are you okay?

08:56.302 --> 08:58.738
- No.
- You're with Mr. Griffin?

08:58.772 --> 08:59.706
- Yeah.
- I have some images

08:59.739 --> 09:00.974
from today's exam.

09:01.007 --> 09:02.809
- W-what--w--

09:02.842 --> 09:05.879
- So what you're looking at
is the ascending colon.

09:05.912 --> 09:09.115
You're gonna see some swelling,
especially in that photo.

09:09.149 --> 09:10.884
Pass that down and make sure
everyone sees it.

09:10.917 --> 09:12.952
- Everyone doesn't need
to see it, that's--

09:12.986 --> 09:14.754
- Wait, but doctor,
why does this one

09:14.788 --> 09:16.022
have a question mark
drawn on it?

09:16.056 --> 09:18.024
- That spot is where
I found a small polyp.

09:18.058 --> 09:20.760
- Wait, a polyp?
- Most polyps are harmless.

09:20.794 --> 09:22.929
We'll run some tests and call
you with the results tomorrow.

09:22.962 --> 09:26.900
- W-w-w-w--
for sure there's a polyp?

09:26.933 --> 09:28.702
- Here, y'all wanna see?
- What are you doing?

09:28.735 --> 09:30.303
Don't pass it to her!
Gimme, gimme, gimme!

09:30.337 --> 09:33.773
Passing--ugh.
And why are you taking it?

09:33.807 --> 09:35.008
That's crazy.

09:35.041 --> 09:39.045
<i>♪ </i>

09:39.079 --> 09:40.847
- Ah-ah-hem!

09:40.880 --> 09:43.049
We'd like to talk to you
all today

09:43.083 --> 09:44.317
about our friendship.

09:44.351 --> 09:47.053
We are hoping
that our words will inspire you

09:47.087 --> 09:49.055
to vote for us
for Whitlock's "Best Friends."

09:49.089 --> 09:50.223
- "Friendship.

09:50.256 --> 09:52.192
"Webster's Dictionary
defines it

09:52.225 --> 09:54.294
"as a person whom one knows

09:54.327 --> 09:56.863
and with whom one--"

09:56.896 --> 09:59.866
[electronic music]

09:59.899 --> 10:01.201
♪

10:01.234 --> 10:02.936
both: Friends!

10:02.969 --> 10:04.004
Friends!

10:04.037 --> 10:06.806
♪

10:06.840 --> 10:08.341
Friends!

10:08.375 --> 10:10.143
both: Besties!

10:10.176 --> 10:12.112
both: Friends!

10:12.145 --> 10:18.318
♪

10:20.153 --> 10:21.855
- They're campaigning
as write-in candidates,

10:21.888 --> 10:23.089
and they're going hard!

10:23.123 --> 10:26.826
- Frickin' do-si-do...
now!

10:26.860 --> 10:33.800
♪

10:39.806 --> 10:42.175
- It's called
The Serendipity.

10:42.208 --> 10:44.844
- Oh. Now, by that
do you mean this moment

10:44.878 --> 10:46.112
or the ring?

10:46.146 --> 10:47.981
- I can't with you!

10:48.014 --> 10:49.983
- I'm sorry that I'm being
so funny and awesome

10:50.016 --> 10:51.985
while you're trying to work.
Tell me about the ring.

10:52.018 --> 10:55.121
- Not until you tell me more
about these plates.

10:55.155 --> 10:57.057
- Oh, my...

10:57.090 --> 10:59.125
Princess Di plates.
Well,

10:59.159 --> 11:00.994
I just always really
admired, you know,

11:01.027 --> 11:03.063
her stance on landmines.

11:03.096 --> 11:04.164
Against.

11:04.197 --> 11:05.965
- Hmm.
Yeah.

11:05.999 --> 11:08.835
- I just started
collecting them

11:08.868 --> 11:10.403
around the same time
that my, uh...

11:10.437 --> 11:13.239
<i>[somber music]</i>
Parents started arguing.

11:13.273 --> 11:15.208
<i>♪ </i>

11:15.241 --> 11:18.845
- You poor, sweet man.

11:18.878 --> 11:22.148
- Would you teach me
Instagram?

11:22.182 --> 11:26.086
- Oh! Somebody help me!

11:26.119 --> 11:28.088
- Helen, are you okay?
- Oh!

11:28.121 --> 11:30.156
I just bopped my face
on my monitor,

11:30.190 --> 11:32.292
and I knocked my tooth out!

11:32.325 --> 11:34.160
- Thank heavens
it's your fake tooth

11:34.194 --> 11:36.029
which can be replaced.

11:36.062 --> 11:37.997
- Well, this one isn't.

11:38.031 --> 11:40.000
- Oh, Helen,
what are you doin'?

11:40.033 --> 11:41.868
You're a wild one,
aren't you?

11:41.901 --> 11:44.237
- Marjorie, Marjorie,
I-I wrote a new song!

11:44.270 --> 11:45.271
Listen to this.

11:45.305 --> 11:46.906
♪ Foot on the gas

11:46.940 --> 11:48.441
♪ And I'm goin' too fast

11:48.475 --> 11:50.443
♪ It's a rock n' roll car,
yeah ♪

11:50.477 --> 11:52.045
- No, don't got in there,
Marjorie.

11:52.078 --> 11:53.947
Stay with me,
and I'll tell you the story

11:53.980 --> 11:56.049
about when I came out
to my grandpa

11:56.082 --> 11:58.051
in the Denny's parking lot
and it went just fine.

11:58.084 --> 12:01.454
- [laughs] What has gotten
into you two goofs, huh?

12:01.488 --> 12:03.990
Because I want whatever
y'all are havin'.

12:04.024 --> 12:05.458
[laughter]

12:05.492 --> 12:08.061
- [sighs]

12:08.094 --> 12:11.064
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

12:11.097 --> 12:18.004
<i>♪ </i>

12:23.410 --> 12:25.011
- Stef, what are you doing?

12:25.045 --> 12:26.880
- Well, I'm making sure
you're okay

12:26.913 --> 12:28.348
while also testing out
some baby products.

12:28.381 --> 12:30.283
- Wait a minute--I wasn't
wearing pajamas before.

12:30.316 --> 12:31.951
Did you change me?

12:31.985 --> 12:34.988
- Yes, we changed you.
Don't get weird.

12:35.021 --> 12:38.158
- Jack, you own
"Fifty Shades of Grey"?

12:38.191 --> 12:40.927
all: Ooh!
Freaky-deaky!

12:40.960 --> 12:43.930
- All right, okay, there was
a month where everyone got it!

12:43.963 --> 12:45.932
I-I didn't get
the other shades!

12:45.965 --> 12:48.268
Look, can you guys just
stop poking around my home?

12:48.301 --> 12:49.903
I'm feeling a little...

12:49.936 --> 12:52.272
- Oh, um...vulnerable?

12:52.305 --> 12:54.174
- Whoops.
- Actually, those are mine.

12:54.207 --> 12:55.975
Those are my gym panties.

12:56.009 --> 12:57.344
They must have fallen
outta my coat pocket.

12:57.377 --> 12:59.512
- Oh, is that--
- Look, enough!

12:59.546 --> 13:02.015
Look, this day
has been a nightmare

13:02.048 --> 13:04.217
from start to finish, okay?
I just wanna be alone.

13:04.250 --> 13:06.086
- Well, we're not
leaving you alone, okay?

13:06.119 --> 13:08.088
We're gonna stay here
and tease you

13:08.121 --> 13:10.256
and help you forget
about that scary test.

13:10.290 --> 13:12.992
- When Keith gets scared,
I sing to him.

13:13.026 --> 13:15.161
♪ Don't you cry,
little doggie ♪

13:15.195 --> 13:17.263
- Stop!
No!

13:18.431 --> 13:20.500
- Okay, we get it.

13:20.533 --> 13:22.102
You don't like to be
goofed on.

13:22.135 --> 13:24.237
You don't like dog songs.
What do you like?

13:24.270 --> 13:28.408
- I like getting revenge
on those who've wronged me.

13:28.441 --> 13:31.511
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

13:31.544 --> 13:34.014
<i>♪ </i>

13:34.047 --> 13:36.282
- Oh, yeah,
that woman's got to pay.

13:36.316 --> 13:38.151
[line ringing]

13:38.184 --> 13:41.087
<i>Agatha: Leave your name</i>
<i>and number after the beep</i>

13:41.121 --> 13:43.156
<i>and try not to mumble</i>
<i>like a moron.</i>

13:43.189 --> 13:44.991
- Oh.
[beep]

13:45.025 --> 13:46.993
- Hi, I'm a mermaid.

13:47.027 --> 13:48.495
My name is...

13:48.528 --> 13:51.164
Eeeeeeeee!
Eee-ee-ee--

13:51.197 --> 13:54.034
- [Russian accent] Hello.
I am snow saleswoman.

13:54.067 --> 13:57.537
I will put you in igloo
today, uh...

13:57.570 --> 14:01.508
[normal voice] No, I--I'm--I
wanna order a pizza, actually.

14:01.541 --> 14:03.343
And, um, with, um...

14:03.376 --> 14:05.979
I can't think of any toppings!

14:06.012 --> 14:08.982
[beep]
- I was referred to you by...

14:09.015 --> 14:11.051
[groans]
Arrrrrhhhhh...

14:11.084 --> 14:13.186
[beep]
- Hello, my name is

14:13.219 --> 14:16.156
Peabody J. Taco
of the hard shell Tacos.

14:16.189 --> 14:18.024
[beep]
- Would you accept

14:18.058 --> 14:19.459
a Groupon that expired in

14:19.492 --> 14:22.395
[grunting]
Urr! Uhh-Ooh-Oohhhh!

14:22.429 --> 14:25.398
- [Russian accent]
It is saleswoman of the snow.

14:25.432 --> 14:27.500
And I sell the snow
by the flake.

14:27.534 --> 14:31.204
Everyone is different.
Oh, no, pepperoni!

14:31.237 --> 14:34.074
Pepperoni! Pep, please--
Oh, ah--bye.

14:34.107 --> 14:36.242
[laughter]
- Oh, my God.

14:36.276 --> 14:38.511
- [Irish accent]
Oh, Molly, I love ya.

14:38.545 --> 14:41.081
Come to da poob
and tip da pint!

14:41.114 --> 14:42.482
- What kind of accent
is that?

14:42.515 --> 14:44.084
- Irish.

14:44.117 --> 14:46.319
- Uh-uh, girl,
that was full-on pirate.

14:46.353 --> 14:48.355
[beep]
- This is Horace T. Taco

14:48.388 --> 14:50.357
of the soft shell Tacos.

14:50.390 --> 14:52.225
Perhaps you know
my arch nemesis--

14:52.258 --> 14:53.493
<i>- The mailbox is full</i>
<i>and cannot accept</i>

14:53.526 --> 14:55.362
<i>any messages at this time.</i>
- It's full.

14:55.395 --> 14:57.030
<i>- Good-bye.</i>
- It's full--we did it.

14:57.063 --> 14:59.099
- Yes!
- Yes!

14:59.132 --> 15:00.467
- Ah!

15:00.500 --> 15:02.602
- Nice.

15:02.635 --> 15:05.271
You guys wearing
my sweatpants?

15:05.305 --> 15:08.441
<i>♪ </i>

15:08.475 --> 15:12.545
[indistinct chatter]

15:12.579 --> 15:15.148
- You think you're bester
friends than us?

15:16.516 --> 15:18.551
- We challenge you
to a duel

15:18.585 --> 15:20.286
that we hope
that we will win.

15:20.320 --> 15:22.122
- Fine.
- Sounds good.

15:23.656 --> 15:25.291
- All right, everybody,

15:25.325 --> 15:27.527
just three questions left.

15:27.560 --> 15:29.562
Let's take a little trip
to Tinseltown.

15:29.596 --> 15:33.533
Victor, what is Eduardo's
favorite movie?

15:33.566 --> 15:35.435
- Oh, that's an easy one.
It used to be "Shanghai Noon,"

15:35.468 --> 15:37.137
but now he can't
fall asleep at night

15:37.170 --> 15:39.205
without watching
"Pitch Perfect 2."

15:39.239 --> 15:41.307
Wait--does that mean
he hates "Pitch Perfect 2"

15:41.341 --> 15:43.076
because
it puts him to sleep?

15:43.109 --> 15:44.678
- I'm gonna need
a final answer, buddy.

15:44.711 --> 15:47.347
- Uh, "Shanghai Noon."
Final answer.

15:47.380 --> 15:49.249
- Eduardo.

15:49.282 --> 15:51.351
- Oh, my God!
- Come on, man!

15:51.384 --> 15:53.286
- We talked a bunch
about how the young women

15:53.319 --> 15:55.422
really find their stride
in the sequel.

15:55.455 --> 15:58.692
- All right, Grace, it is time
to ride the rainbow.

15:58.725 --> 16:01.294
What's Anthony's
favorite color?

16:01.327 --> 16:04.698
- Um, his shirt is blue,

16:04.731 --> 16:07.300
so...blue?

16:07.334 --> 16:08.535
- Yes!

16:08.568 --> 16:09.669
You literally see me!

16:09.703 --> 16:11.371
I love my BFF!

16:11.404 --> 16:13.440
- My man!

16:13.473 --> 16:15.442
- It's time for
the last question.

16:15.475 --> 16:19.112
Eduardo, let's talk grub,
bub.

16:19.145 --> 16:21.247
What is Victor's favorite food?

16:21.281 --> 16:23.149
- Pot pie.
- What?

16:23.183 --> 16:24.651
- Pot pie--
you said just Friday

16:24.684 --> 16:26.486
that my mother's pot pie
was the best in the world.

16:26.519 --> 16:28.621
- It's pizza.
It's pizza!

16:28.655 --> 16:30.256
It's always pizza!

16:30.290 --> 16:31.658
- Ooh!
- Ooh...

16:31.691 --> 16:33.360
- Eduardo, we're teens!

16:33.393 --> 16:35.528
We're like two decades out
from lovin' pot pie.

16:35.562 --> 16:37.430
- Then why did Victor
say that to my mother

16:37.464 --> 16:39.132
about her pot pie?

16:39.165 --> 16:41.267
- I was being nice!

16:41.301 --> 16:43.203
- Let's give it up
for our best friends...

16:43.236 --> 16:45.338
[cheers and applause]

16:45.372 --> 16:50.310
<i>♪ </i>

16:50.343 --> 16:53.546
- Helen, I know
it's been awkward, so...

16:53.580 --> 16:55.482
I'm just gonna come out
and say it.

16:55.515 --> 16:58.485
Today is Marjorie's last day
and...

16:58.518 --> 17:00.387
I think you should
ask her out.

17:00.420 --> 17:01.621
I mean, your eyes light up

17:01.654 --> 17:03.323
whenever she walks into
the room!

17:03.356 --> 17:06.292
- Yes, Marjorie
makes my nether regions

17:06.326 --> 17:08.395
thump the "Law & Order" theme,

17:08.428 --> 17:10.463
but I couldn't do that
to you, Ralph.

17:10.497 --> 17:13.266
This is the first time
that you've flirted with anyone

17:13.299 --> 17:15.502
since your divorce.

17:15.535 --> 17:17.537
I would rather die again.

17:17.570 --> 17:19.472
- Oh, hi, Helen!

17:19.506 --> 17:22.208
I have an extremely important
question to ask you.

17:22.242 --> 17:24.244
If I said you had
a nice body,

17:24.277 --> 17:25.545
would you hold it
against me?

17:25.578 --> 17:27.447
- Oh, it's a riddle?

17:27.480 --> 17:29.482
Oh, uh...
of course I would

17:29.516 --> 17:32.519
hold my body against you,
Marjorie,

17:32.552 --> 17:34.654
and so would Ralph!

17:34.688 --> 17:36.589
- Ah! Both of you, huh?

17:36.623 --> 17:39.526
'Cause that sounds like
my kinda party!

17:39.559 --> 17:41.761
Well, maybe I'll swing by
later and we can, uh,

17:41.795 --> 17:44.431
get into some trouble
together?

17:44.464 --> 17:47.300
[chuckles]
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

17:50.537 --> 17:52.439
- ♪ Dun-dun

17:52.472 --> 17:55.608
- Did she just propose
what I think she did?

17:55.642 --> 17:57.410
- I think so.

17:57.444 --> 17:59.412
A three-way at work.

17:59.446 --> 18:00.513
Well, it's official.

18:00.547 --> 18:01.681
I'm turning into my mother.
[chuckles]

18:01.715 --> 18:03.450
- But we--we--
we can't!

18:03.483 --> 18:05.218
I mean, right?

18:05.251 --> 18:07.654
- No! I mean, we can't
look at each other naked.

18:07.687 --> 18:10.357
- We're gonna say, "Marjorie,
we'll do things with you,

18:10.390 --> 18:12.792
but not with each other?"
That's just weird!

18:12.826 --> 18:15.362
- Dear Marjorie,
here's 102 rules

18:15.395 --> 18:17.397
before we start smoochin'.

18:17.430 --> 18:19.366
I mean, we could do
less rules, but...

18:19.399 --> 18:21.301
[laughing] No, forget it!
- [laughing]

18:21.334 --> 18:23.269
- Oh, no, that's crazy,
right?

18:23.303 --> 18:24.437
- Whoo!
- Ha ha ha ha.

18:24.471 --> 18:26.272
What?

18:26.306 --> 18:29.743
[laughter continues]

18:32.746 --> 18:36.249
[loud, forced laugh]

18:36.282 --> 18:37.751
[sighs]

18:37.784 --> 18:40.453
<i>♪ </i>

18:40.487 --> 18:44.824
- Hi, um, I'm calling for
the results of my colonoscopy.

18:44.858 --> 18:46.292
Jack Griffin.

18:46.326 --> 18:47.394
<i>- Mr. Griffin,</i>

18:47.427 --> 18:50.697
I received 127 messages

18:50.730 --> 18:54.401
<i>from what sounded like you</i>
<i>and your loud friends.</i>

18:54.434 --> 18:56.269
[laughing]
<i>Unfortunately,</i>

18:56.302 --> 18:58.505
all of those messages
flooded our system

18:58.538 --> 19:01.675
and deleted your test results
to make space.

19:01.708 --> 19:03.343
- Wait, wait, wait.

19:03.376 --> 19:05.745
Voicemails deleted
a test result?

19:05.779 --> 19:06.746
H--that can't be a thing.

19:06.780 --> 19:09.482
<i>- You'll need to get</i>
<i>another colonoscopy</i>

19:09.516 --> 19:12.385
tomorrow morning
to be absolutely certain

19:12.419 --> 19:13.887
<i>you're cancer-free.</i>

19:13.920 --> 19:17.791
I hope you and your friends
had fun, Mr. Taco.

19:17.824 --> 19:21.728
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

19:21.761 --> 19:24.798
- She knows it was us
who did the prank calls.

19:24.831 --> 19:26.633
She's making me do the test
again.

19:26.666 --> 19:29.302
- That sucks!
- Damn!

19:29.336 --> 19:30.637
Well, I guess she won.

19:30.670 --> 19:33.773
- [sucks tongue]
Or maybe not.

19:33.807 --> 19:36.876
But it's gonna cost me
my last shred of dignity.

19:36.910 --> 19:38.578
<i>♪ </i>

19:42.882 --> 19:46.486
<i>[dark music]</i>

19:46.519 --> 19:49.422
- Aren't you forgetting
something?

19:50.523 --> 19:51.791
- [sighs]

19:53.993 --> 19:56.496
- [clears throat]
In the end,

19:56.529 --> 19:58.832
the winners of
the "Best Friends" category

19:58.865 --> 20:00.700
were the write-in candidates.

20:00.734 --> 20:03.503
- Yes! You do the work,
you get the reward!

20:03.536 --> 20:05.372
Oh!
- Actually, I meant Ashley

20:05.405 --> 20:07.774
and Amanda.
- Yes! Ohh!

20:07.807 --> 20:09.409
They're back, baby.

20:09.442 --> 20:12.512
<i>[melancholy music]</i>

20:12.545 --> 20:16.750
<i>♪ </i>

20:16.783 --> 20:18.852
- Here,
you take these.

20:18.885 --> 20:21.921
- Ours was a sham
friendship anyways.

20:21.955 --> 20:23.990
You two are the real BFFs.

20:24.024 --> 20:26.526
- We don't deserve
your used hats.

20:26.559 --> 20:28.728
[softly]
I said pot pie.

20:28.762 --> 20:30.797
- Come on, you're Victuardo.

20:30.830 --> 20:35.602
<i>♪ </i>

20:35.635 --> 20:37.637
- During last night's
closing statements

20:37.671 --> 20:39.606
of "Bunkbed Breakdown,"

20:39.639 --> 20:41.474
we agreed that you guys
could be, like,

20:41.508 --> 20:43.710
actual best friends.

20:43.743 --> 20:47.013
It seems like you have a real
special thing gestating.

20:47.047 --> 20:49.683
- Then my brother threw up
and Victor had to go home.

20:50.817 --> 20:52.619
- Okay.

20:52.652 --> 20:55.789
<i>♪ </i>

20:57.590 --> 20:59.993
- Although I am thrilled

21:00.026 --> 21:02.629
that your loud,
obnoxious friends aren't here,

21:02.662 --> 21:04.731
you do need to have
a ride present,

21:04.764 --> 21:07.467
so you'll have to continue
to fast

21:07.500 --> 21:10.036
and come back tomorrow
and take the test again.

21:10.070 --> 21:11.971
- Yeah, no.

21:12.005 --> 21:13.606
I<i>have</i>a ride.

21:15.942 --> 21:18.578
[louder]
I have a ride!

21:18.611 --> 21:20.647
- Whoo-hoo!
[laughing]

21:20.680 --> 21:22.916
- Ah!
- Oh, no...

21:22.949 --> 21:25.952
Oh, this is not--
- No, this is it.

21:25.985 --> 21:28.688
- No, no, no, no.
- These are my friends.

21:28.722 --> 21:30.657
- This is completely
illegal.

21:30.690 --> 21:32.525
You can't just come in
here like this.

21:32.559 --> 21:34.060
No!
[everyone whooping]

21:34.094 --> 21:35.829
No, no, no, no, no,
no, no.

21:35.862 --> 21:37.664
This is illegal!

21:37.697 --> 21:40.600
[overlapping shouting,
cheering]

21:40.633 --> 21:42.035
No! Enough!
- No?

21:42.068 --> 21:43.003
- Enough!
- Oh.

21:43.036 --> 21:45.071
- Stop!

21:45.105 --> 21:47.507
You want your results?
Fine.

21:49.642 --> 21:52.545
Everything was clear.

21:52.579 --> 21:55.715
And I'm happy to share it
with everyone.

21:55.749 --> 21:59.085
<i>♪ </i>

21:59.119 --> 22:00.920
[all whooping]

22:00.954 --> 22:04.090
Please stop.
Just go.

22:04.124 --> 22:06.760
No, no.
Please go away.

22:06.793 --> 22:08.528
- Ohh...

22:08.561 --> 22:09.796
Hi!
- Wow.

22:09.829 --> 22:11.564
- Oh, so glad you made it.

22:11.598 --> 22:12.966
- So that's you there,
huh?

22:12.999 --> 22:15.001
- That's me!
- Mmm!

22:15.035 --> 22:16.703
Well, I'm glad you're healthy.
- Mm-hmm.

22:16.736 --> 22:18.872
- Maybe next time I could
give you a ride, huh?

22:18.905 --> 22:20.106
- Okay.

22:20.140 --> 22:22.108
Hey, um, you wanna
know something

22:22.142 --> 22:24.678
that's even more humiliating
than this?

22:24.711 --> 22:25.945
- What?

22:25.979 --> 22:27.881
- I own
"Fifty Shades of Grey."

22:29.716 --> 22:31.051
- We all bought it
that month.

22:31.084 --> 22:33.086
- Yeah.
- You...

22:33.119 --> 22:35.689
you did buy it
that month, right?

22:36.956 --> 22:39.526
- Yeah!

22:39.559 --> 22:41.795
- Hey, the whole school's
having a party

22:41.828 --> 22:44.130
at my gastroenterologist's
and I'm not even invited?

22:44.164 --> 22:45.865
[scoffs] Oof!

22:45.899 --> 22:48.001
<i>♪ </i>

22:48.034 --> 22:49.602
- Y'all rascals here?

22:49.636 --> 22:51.504
I'm heading out.

22:52.639 --> 22:54.140
Oh.

22:54.174 --> 22:55.875
[chuckles]

22:55.909 --> 22:58.011
[sniffs]
Mmm.

22:58.044 --> 23:01.648
<i>- Dearest Marjorie,</i>
<i>it's me, Ralph.</i>

23:01.681 --> 23:04.884
<i>- And me, Helen.</i>
<i>I'm the purple pen.</i>

23:04.918 --> 23:07.754
<i>We think you're the best thing</i>
<i>since sliced ham.</i>

23:07.787 --> 23:09.122
<i>Ralph:</i>
<i>And you've made me excited</i>

23:09.155 --> 23:11.591
<i>about the idea</i>
<i>of being single.</i>

23:11.624 --> 23:14.761
<i>But because we are long-time</i>
<i>friends and coworkers...</i>

23:14.794 --> 23:16.596
<i>Helen: We respectfully</i>
<i>decline your offer</i>

23:16.629 --> 23:18.832
<i>of a sex three-way.</i>

23:18.865 --> 23:20.633
<i>Ralph: You could just say</i>
<i>three-way.</i>

23:20.667 --> 23:21.968
<i>Helen: Well, you could just</i>
<i>tell me that</i>

23:22.002 --> 23:23.036
<i>instead of writing it down.</i>

23:23.069 --> 23:24.204
<i>Ralph: Let's just start over!</i>

23:24.237 --> 23:26.973
<i>Helen: This is my only piece</i>
<i>of stationary, Ralph.</i>

23:27.007 --> 23:28.742
<i>Ralph: What about</i>
<i>the stationary with the cat</i>

23:28.775 --> 23:29.776
<i>dressed as Shakespeare?</i>

23:29.809 --> 23:30.910
<i>Helen: Well, that's tucked</i>

23:31.945 --> 23:32.879
<i>under the copier</i>
<i>so it doesn't rattle.</i>

23:33.580 --> 23:34.681
<i>Hey, are you hungry?</i>

23:35.782 --> 23:35.815
<i>Ralph: I could use a bowl</i>
<i>of chili right now.</i>

23:36.216 --> 23:37.550
<i>Shall we?</i>
